sql:
SELECT SUM(quantity) AS total_cards_in_deck
FROM deck_cards
WHERE deck_id = 1;

SELECT deck_name
FROM decks
ORDER BY win_rate DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "Leading stars of victory" refers to the top-performing cards;
- "Elevates the deck's success rate above the golden threshold of 75%" means a win rate with the card greater than 75%;
- "Showcasing their dominance in the arena" signifies that these cards are among the best performers within the context of the game or tournament.

sql:
SELECT user_id, total_wins
FROM users
ORDER BY total_wins DESC;

SELECT deck_name
FROM decks
WHERE win_rate > 0.8;

external_knowledge:
Seasoned players: Those users with a significant experience level in games;
Threshold of experience: Represents a milestone of participation, here defined as having at least 10 game sessions;
A decade's worth of voyages: Metaphorically refers to having participated in at least 10 game sessions.

sql:
SELECT AVG(win_rate) AS average_win_rate
FROM decks
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT card_name, AVG(mana_cost) AS average_mana_cost
FROM cards
GROUP BY card_name;

SELECT card_name, mana_cost
FROM cards
WHERE mana_cost = (SELECT MAX(mana_cost) FROM cards);
